  "chapter": {
    "number": 51,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Salvation for Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Listen to Me, you who pursue righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you who seek the LORD:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Look to the rock from which you were cut,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to the quarry from which you were hewn.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Look to Abraham your father,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to Sarah who gave you birth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When I called him, he was but one;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then I blessed him and multiplied him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the LORD will comfort Zion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will look with compassion on all her ruins;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will make her wilderness like Eden",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and her desert like the garden of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Joy and gladness will be found in her,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "thanksgiving and melodious song.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pay attention to Me, My people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and listen to Me, My nation;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for a law will go out from Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My justice will become a light to the nations;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will bring it about quickly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My righteousness draws near,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My salvation is on the way,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and My arms will bring justice to the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The islands",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2686
          },
          {
            "text": "will look for Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wait in hope for My arm.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lift up your eyes to the heavens,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and look at the earth below;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for the heavens will vanish like smoke,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the earth will wear out like a garment,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and its people will die like gnats.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But My salvation will last forever,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My righteousness will never fail.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen to Me, you who know what is right,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you people with My law in your hearts:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not fear the scorn of men;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not be broken by their insults.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the moth will devour them like a garment,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the worm will eat them like wool.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But My righteousness will last forever,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My salvation through all generations.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Awake, awake,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "put on strength, O arm of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Wake up as in days past,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as in generations of old.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Was it not You who cut Rahab to pieces,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who pierced through the dragon?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Was it not You who dried up the sea,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the waters of the great deep,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who made a road in the depths of the sea",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the redeemed to cross over?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So the redeemed of the LORD will return",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and enter Zion with singing,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "crowned with everlasting joy.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Gladness and joy will overtake them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sorrow and sighing will flee.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I, even I, am He who comforts you.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Why should you be afraid of mortal man,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "of a son of man who withers like grass?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But you have forgotten the LORD, your Maker,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who stretched out the heavens",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and laid the foundations of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You live in terror all day long",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of the fury of the oppressor",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who is bent on destruction.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "But where is the fury of the oppressor?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The captive will soon be freed;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he will not die in the dungeon,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and his bread will not be lacking.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I am the LORD your God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who stirs up the sea so that its waves roar—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD of Hosts is His name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have put My words in your mouth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and covered you with the shadow of My hand,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to establish",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2687
          },
          {
            "text": "the heavens, to found the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to say to Zion, ‘You are My people.’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Fury Removed"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Awake, awake!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Rise up, O Jerusalem,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you who have drunk from the hand of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the cup of His fury;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you who have drained the goblet to the dregs—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the cup that makes men stagger.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Among all the sons she bore,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no one to guide her;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "among all the sons she brought up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no one to take her hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "These pairs have befallen you:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "devastation and destruction,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "famine and sword.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who will grieve for you?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who can comfort you?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2688
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your sons have fainted;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they lie at the head of every street,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like an antelope in a net.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They are full of the wrath of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the rebuke of your God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore now hear this, you afflicted one,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "drunken, but not with wine.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says your Lord, the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even your God, who defends His people:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“See, I have removed from your hand",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the cup of staggering.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "From that goblet, the cup of My fury,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will never drink again.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will place it in the hands of your tormentors,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who told you: ‘Lie down, so we can walk over you,’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you made your back like the ground,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a street to be traversed.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
